article.headline: Lipscomb 64, Central Florida 63
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Brian Fisk scored 25 points and Lipscomb held off a furious rally for a 64-63 victory over Central Florida on Tuesday night. An intentional foul by Joe Peters with four seconds left sent Kingsley Edwards to the line for UCF (12-7, 5-6 Atlantic Sun Conference), where he hit both. Edwards took the inbound pass on the ensuing possession, but missed the final shot of the game. Corey King made two free throws to put Lipscomb (10-7, 5-5) up 58-39 -- the largest lead of the game -- with 3:33 left. A UCF rally brought them within 64-61 with four seconds left, but they couldn't overcome the Bisons. The 22-6 run included several 3-pointers, hitting 6 of 12 in the second half, and several forced turnovers. Anthony Williams scored 14 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for the Golden Knights. Edwards added 13 points and Joshua Peppers 12.
